cs.CV, cs.DM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a method for subgraph matching using contextual similarities computed through a tensor product graph. This approach is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since subgraph matching is a common problem in these fields. The use of random walks and graph structures also suggests relevance to data mining (cs.DM) and social networks (cs.SI).
